<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-30T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-30T02:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5342: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-30T15:00:00+08:00">July 30, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 30—5:58 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>634. Legation’s 605, July 22, 2 p.m.<note n="89" xml:id="d333fn89">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from American Consul at Chefoo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“July 29, 4 p.m. Commissioner of Customs informed me this
                                    afternoon Liu Chen-nien is desirous of taking over local
                                    customhouse on his own account but was informed that such action
                                    might: <list>
                                        <item>First, raise international complications;</item>
                                        <item>Second, local customs staff including Commissioner
                                            would walk out;</item>
                                        <item>Third, difficulty with coast lights;</item>
                                        <item>Fourth, difficulty with consuls and fact that there
                                            would be difficulty of carrying on because there is no
                                            one to replace present employees.”</item>
                                    </list></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>